# Scenario: Deep nesting (multi-level joins)
# Why: Ensures the compiler correctly handles nested fields that require joins and flattens them into the output map.
query 'CALL graphql::explain("query { transactions { hash from { address owner { name } } } }")'
---
> +-------+--------+---------------------------------------+
> |  idx  |  kind  |                detail                 |
> +-------+--------+---------------------------------------+
> |   0   |  From  |             transactions              |
> |   1   |  Join  |             natural from              |
> |   2   |  Map   |  hash, from_address, from_owner_name  |
> +-------+--------+---------------------------------------+
>
